      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That analogy of a totaled car perfectly captures how hopeless this feels, and it's understandable why you'd feel that way. When things feel completely broken, the idea of \"fixing\" them seems impossible. Instead of trying to fix yourself, perhaps you could explore finding a different way to *be* with this feeling, or finding a way to simply rest from the constant effort. There are different paths to healing than just \"fixing\" what's broken.",
      "source": "target",
